</div><div class="column mcb-column one column_column  column-margin-"><div class="column_attr clearfix"  style=""><div class="google_font" style="font-family:'Open Sans',Arial,Tahoma,sans-serif;font-size:18px;line-height:18px;font-weight:400;letter-spacing:px;color:#626262;">Latest Deal:</div>

<hr class=" hr_color" style="margin: 0 auto 15px;"/>

 
<p>My clients got outbid on the home of their dreams.  I persistently followed up with the agent in the following weeks. The minute that home did fall out of escrow, I was the first one to find out and alert my clients. By then my clients were already in contract on another house, which we had found acceptable but did not like nearly as much. Within hours I got them out of the old contract and into a contract on their dream house. I even managed to recover part of the deposit thanks to my negotiations skills and persistence.</p>
 
<p>I could have easily opted to not pass along the information to my clients, since they were already in a contract that was closing soon, and I was going to get paid. However, my main focus, and one of the primary reasons I love my job, is helping people achieve their dreams. I was more than willing and happy to do the extra work because I knew getting them into their dream house would be the best possible outcome and would make them very happy.</p><br />
 
<div class="google_font" style="font-family:'Open Sans',Arial,Tahoma,sans-serif;font-size:18px;line-height:18px;font-weight:400;letter-spacing:px;color:#626262;">Client Perspective:</div>


<hr class=" hr_color" style="margin: 0 auto 15px;"/>

 
<p>"We were selling an attractive house in a challenging location in Oakland. Thanks to Courtneys efforts, we had some of the busiest Open House weekends even for the hot Oakland market with over 200 people coming through, resulting in several offers. Courtney improved the top offer from the original amount to beat our expectations. We were happy.  When cracks appeared in the first offer in the closing process, Courtney negotiated our back up offer to top the first offer by a significant amount, with no contingencies. We could not believe it  we were better off with the back up offer after all!</p>
 
<p>Throughout the extended closing process she followed up with us almost daily and nudged the selling agent and mortgage broker to perform (even during her vacation). While the closing got delayed due to factors outside of our control, we got extended free rent-back as a compensation thanks to our agent, which gave us enough time to find and purchase a new house.</p>
 
<p>Courtneys drive and tenacity are unmatched; her negotiation skills are very impressive. She is a great agent and a good generous person who is motivated by helping people. She certainly helped us. We are very grateful and so impressed. Go Tigress!"</p>

<p>- Anya Shapina & Lawrence Sutten</p></div></div></div></div></div></div><div class="section mcb-section   " id="contact" style="padding-top:80px; padding-bottom:30px; background-color:" ><div class="section_wrapper mcb-section-inner"><div class="wrap mcb-wrap one  valign-top clearfix" style="" ><div class="mcb-wrap-inner"><div class="column mcb-column one column_column  column-margin-"><div class="column_attr clearfix align_center"  style=""><h2>LETS MEET AND TALK<br />
